# Person (greeter)

person 25 50 Hello there, and welcome to Classic Stand!--You're currently at your lemonade stand. This is where you'll be spending most of your time.--To the east is the sidewalk, which connects your stand to the market.--At the market, head to the buying station to purchase ingredients like lemons, sugar, water, ice, and salt.--Back at your stand, use the actions station to make lemonade and pour it into cups. Each ingredient prompt will suggest a balanced amount, but you can adjust it if you like. Just know that customers will react to how the drink tastes, so try to keep things balanced!--When customers arrive, they will walk to the customer service counter. Head over there and press enter to open the serve menu. You can serve customers one at a time or all at once. You can even talk to them while you wait, but don't chat too long or they will lose patience and leave.--There are all kinds of customers you might meet. Some are friendly, some are in a rush, and some might even try to steal from you! Keep your eyes open.--You also set your own price per cup at the start of each day. Price too high and customers might refuse to buy. Price fairly and they might even leave a tip!--Keep your customers happy to build your reputation. Let too many walk away unserved or serve them bad lemonade and it's game over.--By the way, you already have a small supply of ingredients to get you started. Press tab to check your inventory, and check the readme for a full list of keyboard shortcuts.--Good luck, and have fun! false

